
[1]amass

   AM'ASS, v.t. [L. massa, a heap or lump; Gr. See mass.]

   1. To collect into a heap; to gather a great quantity; to accumulate;
   as, to amass a treasure.

   2. To collect in great numbers; to add many things together; as, to
   amass words or phrases.

   AM'ASS, n. An assemblage, heap or accumulation. [This is superseded by
                                   Mass.]
